The primary objective of this project is to design and implement a home-based Security Operations Center (SOC) leveraging open-source 
technologies to enable real-time threat detection, log analysis, and behavioral correlation. To support this goal, the project
pursues the following specific objectives:

1. Establish a Functional ELK Stack Environment: Install and configure Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana on a virtualized Ubuntu server 
to serve as the backbone for data ingestion, processing, storage, and visualization.

2. Integrate Endpoint Telemetry Agents: Deploy Filebeat, Winlogbeat, and Auditbeat to collect system logs and security events from both 
Linux and Windows endpoints, enhancing host activity visibility.

3. Configure Log Ingestion and Parsing Pipelines: Set up Logstash pipelines to receive, parse, and enrich log data from Beats agents, 
which is then indexed into Elasticsearch for fast querying and analysis.

4. Simulate Adversary Techniques: Utilize tools such as Atomic Red Team andMetasploit to simulate real-world attack techniques, 
validating detection capabilities and testing how well the system identifies these attack behaviors.

5. Develop Custom Detection Rules: Based on the adversarial simulations, create and fine-tune custom detection rules within Kibana to 
identify abnormal patterns and malicious activities in the collected data.

6. Map Detected Activities to the MITRE ATT&CK Framework: Use the MITRE ATT&CK framework to correlate detected activities with known 
adversary tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTPs), supporting a threat-informed defense strategy.

7. Develop Custom Visualizations and Dashboards in Kibana: Create interactive dashboards and visualizations in Kibana to monitor security 
events, analyze attack patterns, and support investigative workflows.

8. Implement Real-Time Alerting Mechanisms: Configure Kibana Alerts to trigger notifications when predefined thresholds or threat 
patterns are detected. Optionally, integrate ElastAlert to extend alerting capabilities.

9. Ensure Scalability and Minimal Resource Utilization: Optimize the system for performance on limited hardware, ensuring that the SOC is
suitable for deployment in home labs, educational environments, or small-scale operational setups. 

By achieving these objectives, this project aims to demonstrate the practicality and effectiveness of a cost-efficient SOC model tailored 
for hands-on cybersecurity education, technical skill development, and deployment in small-scale operational environments.
